tmux -> terminal multiplexer

cheatsheet
  session
    opening a session 
      `tmux` // default name is numbered
      `tmux new -s <name>`

    detach - `<Ctrl-b> d`
    view sessions - `tmux ls` on the console
    attach - `tmux attach -t <session_name>`
    rename - `tmux rename-session -t <old_name> <new_name>`
    kill - `tmux kill-session <name>`

  window
    indexed from 0
    create new window - `<Ctrl-b> c`
    movement btw windows - `<Ctrl-b> <index>`
    rename window - `<Ctrl-b> ,`
    close window - exit all panes

  pane
    to the right - `<Ctrl-b> %`
    down         - `<Ctrl-b> "`
    movement btw panes - `<Ctrl-b> <arrow_key>`
    close a pane - `exit` on console

